Issues.Body:
* .NET Core Version: 
5.0.421.11614

* Have you experienced this same bug with .NET Framework?: 
No

**Problem description:**
When dotnet5 creates a windowless program, it starts with an error 
There is no error when debugging, everything is normal, and the publishing program is running with an error 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16394348/158196305-9e5c70c3-7511-4cd9-b765-1f1fdc8ed437.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16394348/158196823-ddbb2610-216e-4b07-9f9a-0ae8b6f2182c.png)


**Expected behavior:**
Program starts normally 

**Minimal repro:**
```static class Program
    {
        /// <summary>
        ///  The main entry point for the application.
        /// </summary>
        [STAThread]
        static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            MessageBox.Show("test");
            Application.Run();
    }
